Motherhood lately:
It’s crazy how time flies because not so long ago, I became a mom to the most amazing baby boy. Here we are 3 months later and wow, he’s grown so much 🥹 He brings out the softest version of me. 
Postpartum depression doesn’t get talked about enough. Missing who you were and the life you had before you had a baby. Wondering if and when you would get back to feeling like you again. It’s okay to feel like that.  Adjusting to motherhood doesn’t happen overnight. If anything, it motivates you to be the best version of yourself. Being able to workout again saved me. It felt so good to be back at a place I was at more than anywhere else. To the friends and family who were there for me during my most vulnerable time, I want to thank you so much.
To all of the mommies, you’re doing an excellent job. Continue to give yourself grace. I promise you, your work never goes unnoticed.

Xoxo 💋 Bae✨
